  "prompt": "What is the dress code for fresher girls in Capgemini?",
  "response": "Capgemini, like many other global consulting and technology firms, typically has a business casual dress code. For fresher girls, this means wearing attire that is professional yet comfortable. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Tops**: Blouses, shirts, and sweaters that are neat and professional. Avoid overly casual items like t-shirts with logos or slogans.\n2. **Bottoms**: Dress pants, skirts (knee-length or longer), and tailored trousers are appropriate. Avoid jeans, shorts, or overly tight skirts.\n3. **Dresses**: Professional dresses that are not too short or revealing.\n4. **Footwear**: Closed-toe shoes, flats, low heels, and dressy sandals are generally acceptable. Avoid overly casual footwear like flip-flops or sneakers.\n5. **Accessories**: Keep accessories minimal and professional. Scarves, belts, and simple jewelry are fine, but avoid anything too flashy or distracting.\n\nAlways remember that dress codes can vary slightly depending on the office location and specific department, so it's a good idea to check with your HR or supervisor for any specific guidelines. Furthermore, Capgemini may have \"casual Fridays\" or other relaxed dress days, but these will be communicated by your team or office.",
